nl.fw.yapool

Class PoolPruner

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.fw.yapool.PoolPruner

  • public class PoolPruner
extends Object
    A singleton pool-pruner that can prune multiple pools. It will start/stop itself when pools are added/removed. See also PruneTask.

    The singleton-pattern from Bill Pugh is used as described on WikiPedia

    Author:
    FWiers

      • add

        public boolean add(PrunedPool<?> pool)
        Starts pruning the given pool. If this is the first pruned pool, this pool pruner is started.
        Returns:
        false only if pool's prune interval is less than 0, pool is null or closed.

        public ScheduledExecutorService getExecutor()
        The executor used to schedule prune tasks. If none is set, a default ScheduledThreadPoolExecutor is set when the pruner is started and setShutdownExecutor(boolean) is set to true.

      • isShutdownExecutor

        public boolean isShutdownExecutor()
        If true, shuts down the executor when there are no more pools to prune. Default true if no executor was (explicitly) set via setExecutor(ScheduledExecutorService).
